no.geosoft.jwlf

Class JsonLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.geosoft.jwlf.JsonLog

  • public final class JsonLog
extends Object
    Class representing the content of one JSON Well Log Format log. A log consists of a header, curve definitions, and curve data.
    Author:
    Jacob Dreyer
    See Also:
    https://jsonwelllogformat.org

      • getStep

        public Double getStep()
        Return the regular step of this log.

        NOTE: This property is taken from header, and may not necessarily be in accordance with the actual data on the file.

        Returns:
        The step of the index curve of this log. Null should indicate that the log in irregular or the step is unknown.

      • getActualStep

        public Double getActualStep()
        Return the actual step of the index curve of this log.
        Returns:
        The actual step of the index curve. Null if the log has no data or the log set is irregular.

      • setStep

        public void setStep(Double step)
        Set the regular step of the index curve of this log.
        Parameters:
        step - Step to set. Null to indicate unknown or that the index is irregular. If the log set is time based, the step should be the number of milliseconds between samples.

      • findCurve

        public JsonCurve findCurve(String curveName)
        Return curve of the specified name from this log.

        If there happens to be more than one curve with this name the first one encountered is returned.

        Parameters:
        curveName - Name of curve to find.
        Returns:
        The requested curve, or null if not found.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If curveName is null.

      • findCurveNo

        public int findCurveNo(String curveName)

        If there happens to be more than one curve with this name the first one encountered is returned.

        Parameters:
        curveName - Name of curve to find.
        Returns:
        The requested curve number, or -1 if not found.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If curveName is null.
